      "content": "That makes sense. I have a few clients specifically asking about hair texture, though. Some of the female executives have very natural, tight curls or afro-textured hair, and a few of the men wear traditional head coverings for religious reasons. How should they manage those styles so they still meet that 'structured' and 'symmetric' standard you mentioned without losing their identity?",
